The left hook in the 3rd landed clean and was already sending Wilder down. That right was partly blocked and just grazed the head. And before that in the 3rd after the 1st KD Fury hit Wilder on the chin snapping Wilders head up and to the right and Fury followed it up with a body shot that bout made Wilder shjt himself. And taking a point when Wilder hit Fury repeatedly behind the head but nothing said. And then Christina going on and on about Wilder's equilibrium being so bad off. If it was that was such a factor explain how the fuck to ddid he backpedal around the entire ring for the entire fight? It's hard enough to stand up let alone fight walking backwards round and round the ring.

He even won the 12th minus the pot shot that sent him to the canvas momentarily. But he got up immediately and to land more punches and clearly dictated the pace of the fight. The corner man probably saved Wilder's life. He got mollywopped the entire fight.

Wilder is like Fire
Has a lot of power and very destructive, yet that is the very weakness of fire that made it weak, Overconfidence. Fire moves as if it can overcome everything yet the problem is it's high return but with a very high risk. Wilder's fire haven't been tested much for years and due to being unmatched his fire never grew and became way complacent

Fury was more of water
At first look he seemed balance and at peace which makes most boxers think he is weak, he does not go for the career defining punches but goes for the career defining matches. Like water pretty much Fury becomes anything he put himself into, he utilities his gameplay basing on his opponents tactics which is crucial for boxing. Overall as you can see in this match Fury took what he learned from the first match, as we can see Fury Wilder 1 started a bit well for Wilder yet as the round progresses Fury took the road to his advantage.


Wilder came to the match thinking it was second

snippet.textDisplay: FURY vs WILDER. Fury got it from Antony Joshua commentary: "never make Wilder be comfortable, press him from the beginning till the moment he will quit". Real lesson of boxing. As Fury said, as Joshua often says, Wilder is an easy client. A boxer can’t be there just waiting to land a big right hand. Fury used feints, the jab and the right-hand to touch Wilder, he used also the clinch (the work inside) to make him exhausted with uppercut, short shots and shots on the body, and also to stop explosion from Wilder. Fury will never try the clinch or the work inside against Antony Joshua. Fury will be very far, without the chance of KO. If Joshua decided also to use just jab and long shots as against RUIZ, the fight will be boring.
